description: Borrowed from Dutch vlieboot, but re-analysed as fly +‎ boat.

entries.meaning: A large flat-bottomed Dutch coasting vessel.
examples: a ship of Bristol was chased into this harbour by two Spanish fly-boats, and they report […]  that there are five men of war, Spanish, in the road of Conquet

entries.meaning: A kind of passenger boat formerly used on canals.
